00:45:07.610 --> 00:45:10.270
and saying that even the IMF
has sort of failed to live

00:45:10.270 --> 00:45:13.910
up to what it was meant to do,
which was to rebuild Europe.

00:45:13.910 --> 00:45:17.480
He said now austerity measures,
the things that are doing,

00:45:17.480 --> 00:45:20.630
are actually hurting the
world, not helping it.

00:45:20.630 --> 00:45:23.370
What did you make of his speech?

00:45:23.370 --> 00:45:24.670
And that description?

00:45:24.670 --> 00:45:25.970
&gt;&gt; Christine Lagarde:
Well, first of all,

00:45:25.970 --> 00:45:27.270
I did not read his
entire speech.

00:45:27.270 --> 00:45:29.690
I saw bits and pieces
picked up and, you know,

00:45:29.690 --> 00:45:34.050
I will very carefully
read his speech.

00:45:34.050 --> 00:45:37.590
But, you know, I've heard
this austerity comment made

00:45:37.590 --> 00:45:38.890
in many instances.

00:45:38.890 --> 00:45:41.190
And --

00:45:42.460 --> 00:45:47.010
When we are called upon
to help a country that is

00:45:47.010 --> 00:45:52.150
in very dear financial
difficulties,

00:45:52.150 --> 00:45:54.800
we have to restore stability.

00:45:54.800 --> 00:45:58.670
We have to restore
public finance discipline.

00:45:58.670 --> 00:46:07.540
We have to empower the
authorities with financing.

00:46:07.540 --> 00:46:08.930
That's one thing that we do.

00:46:08.930 --> 00:46:15.020
But we are also an instrument
of macroeconomic sanity.

00:46:15.020 --> 00:46:16.730
Because if we're
called upon to act,

00:46:16.730 --> 00:46:19.360
it's because there
was mismanagement.

00:46:19.360 --> 00:46:23.920
There was poor public
finance organization.

00:46:23.920 --> 00:46:25.990
There was poor monetary policy.

00:46:25.990 --> 00:46:29.140
For multiple reasons, the
situation was not in order.

00:46:29.140 --> 00:46:33.840
And we're trying not to bring
austerity but to bring order.

00:46:33.840 --> 00:46:35.770
So that's number one.

00:46:35.770 --> 00:46:40.030
Number two, if we did
not come in to help,

00:46:40.030 --> 00:46:41.870
the situation would
be even worse.

00:46:41.870 --> 00:46:45.450
Because what happens is when
a country calls for help,

00:46:45.450 --> 00:46:50.570
we come in, we do expect
that public finances will be,

00:46:50.570 --> 00:46:54.940
you know, re-disciplined,
reorganized,

00:46:54.940 --> 00:46:57.310
and that stability will result.

00:46:57.310 --> 00:47:00.470
At which point, investors
come in and say, okay,

00:47:00.470 --> 00:47:03.290
now the situation is stabilized.

00:47:03.290 --> 00:47:05.380
We can come back in
and we can invest.

00:47:05.380 --> 00:47:08.000
So if we did not do that
they simply would not come

00:47:08.000 --> 00:47:10.870
in at that point.

00:47:10.870 --> 00:47:17.120
So I think it's -- we're not the
merchant of austerity, per se,

00:47:17.120 --> 00:47:21.380
we are merchant of trust in
the stability of a system

00:47:21.380 --> 00:47:26.870
that is needed in order
to attract investors,

00:47:26.870 --> 00:47:31.030
generate growth, and, you
know, entail creation of jobs.

00:47:31.030 --> 00:47:35.470
And that's -- we are
the enablers of that.

00:47:35.470 --> 00:47:38.350
